title: Missile Hits Polish Territory Near Ukrainian Border
description: Senior officials in two NATO member states said that a missile hit a Polish village near the Ukrainian border.

title: Biden-Xi Talks Mark Shift in U.S.-China Ties
description: The meeting, arranged through weeks of back-channel negotiations, helped establish new guardrails as differences between the countries widen.

title: World Cup Brings Two Million Visitors and an Epic Culture Clash to Qatar
description: Unaccustomed to Western tourists, wealthy Muslim monarchy hopes to set aside controversies as rowdy fans flood in; the alcohol question.

title: U.S. Panel Calls for Review of China Trade Relations
description: A commission convened by Congress says China engages in unfair trade practices, including subsidizing favored industries and tolerating intellectual property theft.

title: Climate Early-Warning System Aims to Plug Weather Blind Spots
description: The effort by the U.N. and U.S. seeks to improve data collection to better anticipate severe events in parts of Africa, Asia and the Caribbean and Pacific island regions.

title: Iran's Shopkeepers Strike in Support of Protest Movement
description: Shopkeepers across the country closed their stores and went on a planned three-day strike in solidarity with a monthslong protest movement demanding the ouster of the clerical leadership.

title: Looting, Sabotage Marked Last Days of Russia's Occupation of Kherson
description: Even as troops filled trucks with all the looted goods they could find and drove them away, Russian officials told residents they were preparing to fight for the city. Then they knocked out communications and mined the roads.

title: U.S., Allies Announce $20 Billion Package to Wean Indonesia Off Coal
description: Wealthy countries including the U.S. and some of the world’s biggest banks backed a $20 billion funding plan to steer Indonesia, the world’s largest coal exporter, toward renewables as part of efforts to help emerging economies decarbonize.

title: Palestinian Kills Three Israelis, Injures Others in West Bank Attack
description: Three more were injured in the stabbing and car-ramming attack, the latest in a spate of violent incidents in the occupied territory this year.

title: Russian Forces Reposition After Kherson Retreat
description: Russian forces, increasingly exposed to Ukrainian advances, have taken up new positions on the east bank of the Dnipro River, as Moscow’s troops assess new threats following Kyiv’s gains.

title: World's Population Projected to Reach 8 Billion Today
description: Since the 1960s, when the global number of people first hit three billion, it has taken a little over a decade to cross each new billion-person milestone.

title: Israel's Right-Wing Lawmakers Aim to Remake Supreme Court
description: Benjamin Netanyahu’s allies aim to make sweeping changes to Israel’s judicial system, which could allow the passing of laws previously struck down, including bills aimed at expanding settlements in the occupied West Bank.

title: China's Economy Takes a Deeper Hit as Retail Sales Turn Negative
description: China’s economy sank into a deeper funk last month as the weight of strict zero-Covid measures, a real-estate downturn and sinking export demand underscored the difficulties of rekindling growth.

title: Japan's Economy Contracts Slightly in the Third Quarter
description: The world’s third-largest economy contracted for the first time in a year, reflecting weak external demand and a sluggish recovery in private spending.
